      <hedline>
        <hl1>World Briefing | Asia: China: Cities Suffer More Pollution</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By HOWARD W. FRENCH</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">French, Howard W</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Environmental Protection Administration in China says air and water quality in Chinese cities is worsening; says just 38 percent of 585 cities monitored enjoy air quality that reaches minimal national standards (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Air and water quality in Chinese cities is worsening, according to a report of the Environmental Protection Administration. According to the agency's latest survey, just 38 percent of 585 cities monitored enjoyed air quality that reached minimal national standards, down from 45 percent in a 2005 survey.</p>
        <p>HOWARD W. FRENCH</p>
      </block>
